Students learn about twelve years at schools. Schools teach their students different subjects such as math, English, chemistry, etc. In addition, schools prepare their students to be part of their society. They cannot be a helpful elements if they are single-sex schools for two reasons:
First, real life doesn't separate males and female. For example, in universities, hospitals all people need to deal with each other. If boys and girls aren't used to deal with each other, it would be a problem.
Second, relationships between men and women is related to an acquired skills. These skills can have low chance of improving because of the lack of experiences. However, males and females must be in the same place in order to know how to deal with each other in the appropriate way.